entry.summary:
Popover UI elements are common in web apps, offering extra info or options when users interact with something. Usually, developers rely on npm libraries for Popovers, but these increase the project’s bundle size. In this article, I’ll guide you through building a lightweight, reusable Popover component using React and Tailwind CSS — with both click and hover triggers — so you can keep your app fast and flexible without extra dependencies.
